HEADWORD: Calandrinia
<hw>Calandrinia</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a large genus of low-growing
herbs; widespread throughout tropical and warm temperate regions having
usually basal leaves and panicles of purplish ephemeral
flowers.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> genus <gen>Calandrinia</gen>.</syn>⟦br⟧
